### Summary of Changes:

- **Use In-Memory Databases**: I have changed the test database settings to use `':memory:'`. This change ensures that SQLite uses a memory-based database rather than a file-based one, which will significantly reduce the likelihood of a database lock error since memory databases are isolated per connection.

This change should alleviate the problem since each test execution should have its own isolated database. If you have other files or more complex setups, ensure the parallel execution does not inadvertently access the same database file.
